3 March 2017The Justice, Crime Prevention and Security (JCPS) cluster chaired by Minister Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula will on Sunday, 05 March 2017 brief the media on the implementation of the Cluster programme of action for the year, following the 2017 State of the Nation Address. Minister Mapisa-Nqakula will be supported by the Co-Chairperson Minister Nathi Nhleko and members of the Cluster.The briefing will also outline progress that has been made and future plans to achieve the National Development Plan Vision 2030.Members of the media are invited as follows: Date: Sunday, 05 March 2017 Venue: GCIS Pretoria, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street Time: 10h00NB: There will be a video link up to Media Centre, Ground Floor, 120 Plein Street, Parliament, Cape TownNB: Kindly confirm attendance by e-mail to: Ireen Magwai (Pretoria) E-mail: Ireen@gcis.gov.za Cell: 082 440 5676Andile Duka (Cape Town) E-mail: Andiled@gcis.gov.za Cell: 071 154 5619Enquiries: Siphiwe Dlamini Cell: 083 645 4294Issued by Government Communication and Information Systems